title: Biden warns of 'devastating consequences' in push for Trump to sign Covid relief package
description: President-elect Joe Biden has called on President Donald Trump to sign the bipartisan Covid-19 relief bill, warning that any further delay has "devastating consequences" for Americans.

title: Leicester halts Manchester United's away win run
description: Leicester City came from behind twice to deny Manchester United a record-equaling 11th straight English Premier League away win in a 2-2 Boxing Day draw at the King Power Stadium.

title: Female jockey makes history in famous Boxing Day steeplechase
description: Bryony Frost made horse racing history as she became the first woman jockey to win the prestigious King George VI Chase with a "dream" Boxing Day success on 20-1 outsider Frodon.

title: More than half a million people flew in America on Christmas Day
Ancient snack stall uncovered in Pompeii
description: Archaeologists in Pompeii, the city buried in a volcanic eruption in 79 AD, have made the extraordinary find of a frescoed hot food and drinks shop that served up the ancient equivalent of street food to Roman passersby.

title: Woman rescued after car plunges off cliff onto beach
description: A woman was transported in "serious condition" after a car went off a cliff onto a beach in San Francisco on Christmas morning, according to tweets from the city's fire department.

title: Errol Louis: Trump's real target is Section 230
description: CNN political analyst Errol Louis discusses President Donald Trump's opposition to the sweeping defense bill that both chambers of Congress passed by veto-proof majorities, and suggests Trump's "real target" is Section 230.

title: Rep. Waters rails Trump for 'games' amid final stimulus talks
description: Rep. Maxine Waters (D-CA) reacted to President Trump's mixed messaging around the $900 billion relief package that would extend two pandemic unemployment programs and provide the jobless with a $300 weekly federal boost through mid-March.

title: Infamous British-Soviet double agent dies in Moscow
description: The former British spy and Soviet secret agent George Blake has died in Moscow aged 98, according to Russian state-run news agency RIA Novosti.

title: Best-laid plans were derailed by 2020 and pandemic -- even for Vladimir Putin
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin began 2020 with a surprise, sweeping his entire government aside on January 15 after unveiling a raft of constitutional reforms.

title: Scientists discover a new species of snake hiding in plain sight
description: Sometimes, looking at things we thought we knew with fresh eyes (and new tools) can lead to incredible discoveries.

title: Beyoncé to donate $500,000 to people impacted by the eviction crisis
description: Beyoncé will offer $5,000 grants to help people facing foreclosures or evictions due to the housing crisis caused by the coronavirus pandemic.

title: A preschool teacher who was laid off after 20 years won a $250,000 lottery
description: After working as a preschool teacher in Charlotte, North Carolina, for two decades, Joe Camp was laid off in September amid the coronavirus pandemic. A month later, he lost his father.

title: Duke women's basketball cancels rest of season because of Covid-19 concerns
description: Duke University's women's basketball team will not play the remainder of the 2020-2021 season, citing health and safety concerns stemming from Covid-19, the school announced Friday.

title: China turns off the lights in 'Christmas town' as officials race to meet energy targets
description: For months, factories in the city of Yiwu, known as China's "Christmas town," have been cranking out most of the tinsel, decorations and other festive ornaments now hanging on trees worldwide.
